Proper noun

[edit]

Taylor County

One of 67 counties in Florida, United States. County seat: Perry. Named after Zachary Taylor.

One of 159 counties in Georgia, United States. County seat: Butler. Named after Zachary Taylor.

One of 99 counties in Iowa, United States. County seat: Bedford. Named after Zachary Taylor.

One of 120 counties in Kentucky, United States. County seat: Campbellsville. Named after Zachary Taylor.

One of 254 counties in Texas, United States. County seat: Abilene. Named after three brothers who died in the Battle of the Alamo.

One of 55 counties in West Virginia, United States. County seat: Grafton. Named after John Taylor of Caroline.

One of 72 counties in Wisconsin, United States. County seat: Medford. Possibly named after William Robert Taylor.
